You have helped the driver, but he risks an uncertain future if he returns to Galtrev as late as he is.

'Here is another difficulty. I cannot return to Galtrev now. I believe the White Hand Overseers will beat me for my lateness... or worse. They executed my neighbour for losing an important crate bound for Isengard.\n\n'I wish to escape, [placeholder], but if the wood does not arrive, they will make an example of someone else. Will you deliver it?'
Galtrev is not far. The wood that you have brought to Fraid at the Galtrev Lumber-camp can surely be carried the rest of the way.\n\nYou should carry the wood shipment to Galtrev.
'He escaped? Good... that is good. They wanted to kill him for his lateness. But it is the Dragon-clan that they should punish! Why do they not defend us when our warriors are gone?'
Urien is in Galtrev.\n\nYou should speak with Urien now that you have delivered the wood successfully.
